ing as his trailblazing The Carbon Crunch, this volume will be essential reading for anyone concerned with reversing the headlong destruction of our environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEnvironmental economics. 0aNatural resourcesxManagement. 0aNatural resourcesxValuation. 0aSustainable development. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Environmental Economics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021394240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300213942423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300213942/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles